---
import MainLayout from '@/layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Read how Global Events Travels collects, uses, and protects your personal information."
>
  <!-- Page Header -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-secondary-600 to-secondary-500 py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container-custom text-center text-white">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-white/80 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data when you travel with us or use our website.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="prose prose-neutral max-w-none">
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">
          Last updated: {new Date().getFullYear()}
        </p>

        <p>
          This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Global Events Travels</strong> (&quot;we&quot;, &quot;us&quot;, or &quot;our&quot;)
          collects, uses, and protects your information when you visit our website
          <strong>globaleventstravels.com</strong>, make an enquiry, or book a trek, tour, or yatra with us.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>We may collect the following types of personal information:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Basic contact details (name, email address, phone number)</li>
          <li>Booking details (selected trek or package, dates, group size, preferences)</li>
          <li>Communication data (messages you send through forms, WhatsApp, email, or phone)</li>
          <li>Technical data (IP address, browser type, device information, pages visited, and interaction data)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <p>We use your personal data for the following purposes:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>To respond to your enquiries and provide trek or tour recommendations</li>
          <li>To process bookings, reservations, and payments (where applicable)</li>
          <li>To send booking confirmations, pre-departure information, and important updates</li>
          <li>To improve our website, services, and customer experience</li>
          <li>To send optional marketing communication if you have opted in (such as newsletters and offers)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Cookies &amp; Tracking Technologies</h2>
        <p>
          Our website may use cookies and similar technologies to improve performance, analyze traffic,
          and personalize your experience. You can control cookies through your browser settings.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Sharing of Information</h2>
        <p>We do not sell your personal data. We may share your information only when necessary to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Coordinate on-ground services (local guides, transport, accommodation partners)</li>
          <li>Comply with legal obligations or government regulations</li>
          <li>Protect our rights, safety, or property, or that of our customers and partners</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain your personal data only for as long as it is necessary to fulfill the purposes described
          in this Privacy Policy, or as required by law, accounting, or reporting obligations.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Request access to the personal data we hold about you</li>
          <li>Request correction or updating of your information</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your personal data, subject to legal or contractual limitations</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent for marketing communications at any time</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Security</h2>
        <p>
          We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your personal data
          against unauthorized access, misuse, or loss. However, no method of transmission over the
          internet is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Third-Party Links</h2>
        <p>
          Our website may contain links to third-party websites, booking engines, or social media platforms.
          We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of those external sites.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Updates to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or
          for legal, regulatory, or operational reasons. The updated version will always be available
          on this page with a revised &quot;Last updated&quot; date.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or wish to exercise your rights, please contact us at:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Email:</strong> info@globaleventstravels.com</li>
          <li><strong>Phone:</strong> +91 63833 13359</li>
          <li><strong>Website:</strong> globaleventstravels.com/contact</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-xs text-neutral-500 mt-8">
          This page is provided for general informational purposes only and does not constitute legal advice.
          Please consult with a legal professional to review and customize this policy for your specific requirements.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>

